column1: OMAP-12: Organ Mapping Antibody Panel (OMAP) for Multiplexed Antibody-Based Imaging of Retina with IBEX

column24: Stains Muller glia in human retina, key macroglia. This represents a prioritized target for the Retina OMAP.
Multiple cell structures including outer limiting membrane. This represents a prioritized target for the Retina OMAP.

Used to detect Iba1, see above.
Stains bipolar cells in the human retina, core part of visual signalling. This represents a prioritized target for the Retina OMAP.
Stains a subset of ganglion cell nuclei in the human retina.

Stains a subset of bipolar cell nuclei in the human retina.
